cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SOC, cs.CL, cs.DL 

The paper focuses on expert recommendation in online communities, which involves natural language processing, social network analysis, and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which covers research on social networks, online communities, and information retrieval. The paper also uses vector space model and PageRank algorithm, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL) research. Additionally, the paper discusses the influence of candidate experts, which is related to the field of computational social science (cs.SOC). Finally, the paper mentions the use of deep learning techniques, which falls under the category of cs.DL (Machine Learning).
